FBIS3-32980 "drlat033__a94009" FBIS-LAT-94-033-A Document Type:Daily Report 17 February 1994 ANNEX Brazil Government Seeks To Join European Development Bank PY1502135794 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 14 Feb 94 p 11 --FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY PY1502135794 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [From the "Diplomatic Report" column by Luiz Orlando Carneiro] [Text] Like Mexico and Korea, Brazil is seeking to become a full member of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD). The EBRD, which was created to help rebuild Eastern Europe, is chaired by former IMF Managing Director Jacques de Larosiere. Brazilian Ambassador to London Rubens Barbosa has met Larosiere to give him the Brazilian Central Bank's acceptance of an invitation to send representatives to the annual EBRD meeting to be held in St. Petersburg.
